Arrays - are used to store multiple values in a single variable, instead of declaring separate variables for each value.

Declaration - int array[size];
Initialization - int array[size] = {1,2,3}; / int array[] = {1,2,3};
Assignment - array[index] = 1;
Size = sizeof(array) / sizeof(array[0]);

2D Array - int array[row][col];
3D Array - int array[row][col][depth];
Dynamic Array
String Array
Pointer Array
Jagged Array




